{"timestamp":"2026-03-17T12:53:30.220Z","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","session_id":"236f3580-e28b-4dfc-a076-a2a9e5f0a79b","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/236f3580-e28b-4dfc-a076-a2a9e5f0a79b.jsonl","tool_name":"runSubagent","tool_input":{"description":"Explore frontend structure","prompt":"Explore the frontend structure of the linkshortener project at /home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener/frontend/src. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory/file structure under frontend/src\n2. Content of the router/index.ts (or whatever router file exists)\n3. Content of any existing views (list all view files and read their content)\n4. The header component - look for it in components/ or App.vue or layouts\n5. Content of App.vue\n6. Content of any existing layout components\n7. The stores/ directory structure and content\n8. Content of frontend/src/lib/ files\n\nPlease read all these files and return their full content so I can understand the complete picture. Be thorough."},"tool_response":"Here's the complete picture of the frontend structure:\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\nfrontend/src/\n├── App.vue                      ← Root component: fixed header + RouterView\n├── main.ts\n├── style.css\n├── vite-env.d.ts\n├── assets/\n├── components/\n│   └── ui/                      ← shadcn/vue components only\n│       ├── badge/\n│       ├── button/\n│       ├── dialog/\n│       ├── input/\n│       ├── table/\n│       └── tooltip/\n├── lib/\n│   ├── config.ts                ← Env var validation/logging at startup\n│   ├── config.spec.ts\n│   ├── utils.ts                 ← cn() + toDatetimeLocalValue()\n│   ├── utils.test.ts\n│   └── api/                     ← Auto-generated from OpenAPI spec\n│       ├── index.ts\n│       ├── core/                ← ApiError, OpenAPI config, request engine\n│       ├── models/              ← UrlItem, CreateUrlRequestBody, etc.\n│       └── services/\n│           └── DefaultService.ts ← All API calls (logout, register, listUserUrls, createShortenedUrl, updateShortenedUrl, deleteShortenedUrl)\n├── router/\n│   └── index.ts\n├── stores/\n│   ├── auth.ts\n│   ├── auth.spec.ts\n│   ├── theme.ts\n│   ├── theme.spec.ts\n│   ├── urls.ts\n│   └── urls.spec.ts\n└── views/\n    ├── HomeView.vue\n    ├── DashboardView.vue\n    ├── AuthCallbackView.vue\n    └── AuthCallbackView.spec.ts\n```\n\n---\n\n## [router/index.ts](frontend/src/router/index.ts)\n\nThree routes:\n- `/` → `HomeView` (redirects authenticated users to dashboard)\n- `/dashboard` → `DashboardView` (requires auth; redirects to home if not)\n- `/auth/callback` → `AuthCallbackView` (processes OAuth hash fragment)\n\n---\n\n## [App.vue](frontend/src/App.vue)\n\n**There is no separate header component** — the header is inlined directly in `App.vue`. It contains:\n- Fixed top bar (`h-14`) with \"Link Shortener\" title\n- Light/Dark/System theme toggle (3 icon buttons with tooltips)\n- \"Sign In\" / \"Sign Out\" button\n- Sign-in `Dialog` with three OAuth provider buttons (Google, Microsoft, Facebook)\n- `<main class=\"pt-14\"><RouterView /></main>` below\n\n---\n\n## Views\n\n### [HomeView.vue](frontend/src/views/HomeView.vue)\nMinimal — centered page with a heading and tagline. No sign-in UI (that's in App.vue's header).\n\n### [DashboardView.vue](frontend/src/views/DashboardView.vue)\nFull CRUD interface:\n- \"Create Link\" button → `Dialog` form (long URL, optional shortcode, optional expiry)\n- Edit `Dialog` (prefetches fresh data before opening, handles OCC 409)\n- Delete `Dialog` (confirmation with URL details, handles OCC 409)\n- **Desktop**: shadcn `Table` with columns: Short URL, Long URL, Status badge, Expires, Edit/Delete actions\n- **Mobile** (`md:hidden`): Expandable card list with icons for edit/delete\n- Pagination controls (Previous/Next) when `totalPages > 1`\n- Error banners for load/create/update/delete failures\n\n### [AuthCallbackView.vue](frontend/src/views/AuthCallbackView.vue)\nParses `window.location.hash` on mount:\n- `#token=…` → calls `auth.handleCallback()`, redirects to dashboard\n- `#pre_registration_token=…` → shows registration `Dialog` (username input)\n- `#error=…` → shows error message + Go home button\n\n---\n\n## Stores\n\n### [stores/auth.ts](frontend/src/stores/auth.ts)\n- Persists JWT to `localStorage`\n- `handleCallback(jwt)` — decodes JWT payload, sets token + user\n- `login(provider)` — redirects browser to `${BACKEND_URL}/auth/login/${provider}?redirect_to=…`\n- `logout()` — calls `DefaultService.logout()`, clears localStorage and Pinia state\n- Initializes `OpenAPI.TOKEN` from localStorage on store creation\n\n### [stores/urls.ts](frontend/src/stores/urls.ts)\n- State: `items`, `total`, `page`, `pageSize`, `loading`, `error`, `creating`, `createError`, `updating`, `updateError`, `deleting`, `deleteError`\n- `fetchUrls(page, pageSize)` — paginated list load\n- `createUrl({longUrl, shortcode?, expiresAt?})` — creates and refreshes list\n- `updateUrl({id, longUrl, shortcode?, expiresAt?, lastUpdated})` — OCC-aware update (409 shows conflict message + refreshes)\n- `deleteUrl(id, lastUpdated)` — OCC-aware delete\n- `refreshItems()` — silent background refresh (used before dialogs open)\n- `clearCreateError/clearUpdateError/clearDeleteError` — called when dialogs close\n\n### [stores/theme.ts](frontend/src/stores/theme.ts)\n- `ThemeMode`: `'light' | 'dark' | 'system'`\n- Persists to `localStorage` under `'theme'` key\n- Applies `dark` class to `document.documentElement`\n- Listens to `prefers-color-scheme` media query for system mode\n\n---\n\n## [lib/](frontend/src/lib/)\n\n### [utils.ts](frontend/src/lib/utils.ts)\n- `cn(...inputs)` — Tailwind class merge utility (clsx + tailwind-merge)\n- `toDatetimeLocalValue(iso)` — converts ISO string to `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM` for `datetime-local` inputs\n\n### [config.ts](frontend/src/lib/config.ts)\n- `REQUIRED_VARS`: `['LINKSHORTENER_ENV', 'APP_BASE_URL']`\n- `validateConfig()` — throws on missing required vars (called before `app.mount()`)\n- `logConfig()` — logs vars to console, masks secrets in prod mode\n- `SECRET_VARS`: set of vars to mask (JWT_SECRET, SESSION_SECRET, etc.)\n\n### [lib/api/](frontend/src/lib/api/)\nAuto-generated from `openapi/LinkShortener.json`. Key models:\n- `UrlItem`: `{ id, shortcode, long_url, expires_at?, last_updated }`\n- `DefaultService` methods: `logout`, `registerUser`, `listUserUrls`, `createShortenedUrl`, `updateShortenedUrl`, `deleteShortenedUrl`\n\n---\n\n**Key architectural notes:**\n- No layouts folder — `App.vue` serves as the only layout with the inline header\n- No custom components beyond shadcn/vue (in `components/ui/`)  \n- `lucide-vue-next` used for icons throughout\n- OCC (`last_updated` field) is handled in both `updateUrl` and `deleteUrl` in the urls store\n- `OpenAPI.BASE` is set from `APP_BASE_URL` env var in the auth store","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GNUjP1uoDhUvk3j6XzRVvp__vscode-1773735574054","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

