{"timestamp":"2026-03-17T13:07:04.901Z","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","session_id":"71b36e96-30ba-49fa-bbfe-9fc66238657f","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/71b36e96-30ba-49fa-bbfe-9fc66238657f.jsonl","tool_name":"runSubagent","tool_input":{"agentName":"Explore","description":"Frontend account deletion exploration","prompt":"Explore the frontend of a Vue 3 + TypeScript application at /home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener/frontend/ to understand existing patterns for implementing account deletion.\n\nPlease examine:\n1. The `src/stores/` directory - especially the auth store to understand how user info/JWT is managed\n2. The `src/views/` directory - list all files and look at the profile/settings view if it exists\n3. The `src/router/` directory to understand routing\n4. The `src/lib/` directory to understand the API client setup\n5. The `src/components/` directory structure\n6. The `package.json` to understand available dependencies (especially shadcn/vue components)\n7. The `src/App.vue` to understand the app layout\n\nPlease provide:\n- Full content of the auth store\n- Full list of views and their routes\n- Full content of any profile/settings view\n- How the API client is used (example from an existing view)\n- Whether `DELETE /user/account` already exists in the OpenAPI spec / generated client\n- The `openapi/LinkShortener.json` structure (just the paths section to see what's there)\n- How shadcn/vue dialogs/modals are used in existing components (look for examples with AlertDialog or Dialog)\n\nThoroughness: thorough"},"tool_response":"---\n\n## Frontend Architecture Exploration Summary\n\nI've conducted a thorough analysis of the Vue 3 + TypeScript frontend. Here are the key findings:\n\n### 1. **Auth Store** ([auth.ts](frontend/src/stores/auth.ts))\n\n**Full content provided above.** Key patterns:\n- Stores `token` and `user` in refs\n- Decodes JWT payload client-side to extract `user_id` and `user_name`\n- Manages token lifecycle: `setToken()`, `handleCallback()` (decode JWT), `login()` (OAuth redirect), `logout()` (call backend + clear state)\n- Configures the generated API client's `OpenAPI.BASE` and `OpenAPI.TOKEN` automatically\n- Uses `localStorage` for token persistence\n- Error handling: `logout()` catches backend rejections gracefully (non-fatal if token expired)\n\n### 2. **Views & Routes** ([router/index.ts](frontend/src/router/index.ts))\n\n**All views and their routes:**\n- `/` → `HomeView.vue` (public)\n- `/dashboard` → `DashboardView.vue` (requiresAuth)\n- `/profile` → `ProfileView.vue` (requiresAuth)\n- `/profile/settings` → `ProfileSettingsView.vue` (requiresAuth)\n- `/auth/callback` → `AuthCallbackView.vue` (public, processes OAuth hash fragment)\n\nRouter guards: unauthorized users to `/` (except auth callback), authenticated users from `/` → `/dashboard`\n\n### 3. **Profile Settings View** ([ProfileSettingsView.vue](frontend/src/views/ProfileSettingsView.vue))\n\n```vue\n<script setup lang=\"ts\">\nimport { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'\n</script>\n\n<template>\n    <div class=\"container mx-auto px-6 py-8\">\n        <h1 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-6\">Settings</h1>\n        <section class=\"max-w-md space-y-4\">\n            <div>\n                <h2 class=\"text-lg font-semibold text-destructive\">Danger Zone</h2>\n                <p class=\"text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1\">\n                    Once you delete your account, there is no going back. Please be certain.\n                </p>\n            </div>\n            <Button variant=\"destructive\">\n                Delete Account Permanently\n            </Button>\n        </section>\n    </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n**Current state:** Button exists but is not wired to any handler.\n\n### 4. **API Client Usage Pattern**\n\nFrom [urls.ts](frontend/src/stores/urls.ts) (Pinia store):\n```typescript\nimport { DefaultService } from '@/lib/api/services/DefaultService'\n\n// Call pattern:\nconst response = await DefaultService.createShortenedUrl({\n  requestBody: {\n    long_url: params.longUrl,\n    shortcode: params.shortcode,\n    expires_at: params.expiresAt,\n  },\n})\n\n// Error checking pattern:\nif ('status' in response && typeof response.status === 'number') {\n  // ErrorModel response\n  const errMsg = (response as { title?: string }).title ?? 'Failed'\n  return null\n}\n\n// Success processing:\nconst data = response as CreateUrlResponseBody\n```\n\nGenerated client auto-includes Bearer token from `OpenAPI.TOKEN`.\n\n### 5. **OpenAPI Spec — Current Endpoints**\n\n```json\n\"paths\": {\n  \"/auth/logout\": { \"post\": {...} },\n  \"/auth/register\": { \"post\": {...} },\n  \"/r/{shortcode}\": { \"get\": {...} },\n  \"/user/urls\": { \"get\": {...}, \"post\": {...} },\n  \"/user/urls/{id}\": { \"delete\": {...}, \"patch\": {...} }\n}\n```\n\n**`DELETE /user/account` does NOT exist** — this is what needs to be implemented.\n\n### 6. **Dialog/Modal Patterns**\n\n**Available components:** [frontend/src/components/ui/dialog/](frontend/src/components/ui/dialog/)\n- `Dialog.vue` (root wrapper, accepts `v-model:open`)\n- `DialogContent.vue` (styled container with close button)\n- `DialogHeader.vue`, `DialogTitle.vue`, `DialogDescription.vue`\n- `DialogFooter.vue`, `DialogClose.vue`\n\n**Usage example from DashboardView** (delete confirmation pattern):\n\n```vue\n<Dialog :open=\"deleteDialogOpen\" @update:open=\"onDeleteDialogOpenChange\">\n  <DialogContent class=\"sm:max-w-md\">\n    <DialogHeader>\n      <DialogTitle>Delete short link</DialogTitle>\n      <DialogDescription>\n        This action cannot be undone. Please confirm you want to permanently delete the following link.\n      </DialogDescription>\n    </DialogHeader>\n\n    <div class=\"flex flex-col gap-3 py-2\">\n      <!-- Content to confirm -->\n    </div>\n\n    <div v-if=\"urlsStore.deleteError\"\n      class=\"rounded-md bg-destructive/10 border border-destructive/30 px-3 py-2 text-destructive text-sm\">\n      {{ urlsStore.deleteError }}\n    </div>\n\n    <DialogFooter class=\"flex gap-2 pt-2\">\n      <DialogClose as-child>\n        <Button type=\"button\" variant=\"outline\" :disabled=\"urlsStore.deleting\">Cancel</Button>\n      </DialogClose>\n      <Button type=\"button\" variant=\"destructive\" :disabled=\"urlsStore.deleting\" @click=\"submitDelete\">\n        {{ urlsStore.deleting ? 'Deleting…' : 'Delete' }}\n      </Button>\n    </DialogFooter>\n  </DialogContent>\n</Dialog>\n```\n\n### 7. **shadcn/vue Components Available**\n\nFrom `package.json` dependencies:\n- Core: `reka-ui` (headless UI primitives, basis for shadcn/vue)\n- Icons: `lucide-vue-next`\n- Styling: `tailwindcss@^4.2.1`, `tailwind-merge`, `class-variance-authority`\n- State: `pinia`, `vue-router`\n- Table component: `@tanstack/vue-table`\n\n### 8. **App Layout** ([App.vue](frontend/src/App.vue))\n\n- Fixed header (`.fixed top-0 left-0 right-0`) with branding + nav + theme toggle + auth buttons\n- Sign-in dialog in App.vue root (accessible from anywhere)\n- Theme modes: light/dark/system via `useThemeStore`\n- Navigation: Dashboard & Profile links visible when authenticated\n- Logout handler calls `auth.logout()` then redirects to `/`\n\n### 9. **Package.json Dependencies**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"pinia\": \"^3.0.4\",\n    \"reka-ui\": \"^2.9.2\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.5.25\",\n    \"vue-router\": \"^4.6.4\",\n    \"lucide-vue-next\": \"^0.576.0\",\n    \"tailwindcss\": \"^4.2.1\"\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"generate:api\": \"openapi-typescript-codegen --input ../openapi/LinkShortener.json --output src/lib/api --client fetch --useOptions\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Insights for Account Deletion Implementation\n\n1. **Backend**: Need to add `DELETE /user/account` endpoint (Huma registered)\n2. **Frontend API client**: Will be auto-generated once backend endpoint is added\n3. **Store pattern**: Create action in auth store similar to `logout()` but for account deletion\n4. **Dialog pattern**: Use existing Dialog + DialogContent, follow DashboardView delete confirmation layout\n5. **Error handling**: Match `urlsStore` error patterns (show error in dialog, allow retry)\n6. **State management**: Track loading/error states in auth store, disable button during request\n7. **Post-deletion**: Clear all state and redirect to home (like logout)","tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KRoPzJqE9KBKRGTeKPJ5Cx__vscode-1773735574110","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

