{"timestamp":"2026-03-17T13:13:46.698Z","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","session_id":"71b36e96-30ba-49fa-bbfe-9fc66238657f","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/71b36e96-30ba-49fa-bbfe-9fc66238657f.jsonl","tool_name":"memory","tool_input":{"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: Account Deletion Flow\n\n## TL;DR\nImplement `DELETE /user/account` end-to-end: backend interface/repo/handler/route + JWT email claim addition + frontend confirmation dialog with email-matching guard. Test coverage at every layer.\n\n**Decisions:**\n- Email in JWT claims (not a profile endpoint) — user selected this approach\n- No OCC for account deletion (terminal action per backend-business.md §4.1)\n- Admin check: compare ANY provider_email to SUPER_ADMIN_EMAIL via new `FindByUserID` repo method\n- DB cascade handles all child-record deletion (no manual sub-deletes)\n- `CreateJWT` gets new `email string` parameter; all callers updated\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Backend: Repository Interface & Implementation\n\n### Step 1. Add methods to `UserRepository` interface\nFile: `backend/business-logic/interfaces/user_repository.go`\n- Add `FindByUserID(ctx context.Context, userID int64) (*models.User, *models.UserProvider, error)` — returns user + primary provider (earliest created_at). Used for admin check in handler.\n- Add `DeleteUser(ctx context.Context, userID int64) error` — deletes Users row only; DB cascade removes children.\n\n### Step 2. Implement in concrete repository\nFile: `backend/infrastructure/pg/repositories/user_repository.go`\n- `FindByUserID`: SELECT from UserProviders WHERE user_id = ? ORDER BY created_at ASC LIMIT 1, then call private `findUserByID`. Map with pgmappings.*ToBusinessModel.\n- `DeleteUser`: NewDelete on Users WHERE id = ?; check RowsAffected > 0 else return ErrNotFound.\n\n### Step 3. Update mock\nFile: `backend/business-logic/interfaces/mocks/mock_user_repository.go`\n- Manually add `FindByUserID` and `DeleteUser` mock methods following the existing gomock patterns already in the file (note: file is generated but manual additions acceptable per project).\n\n### Step 4. Add repository tests\nFile: `backend/infrastructure/pg/repositories/user_repository_test.go`\n- Test `FindByUserID`: existing user → returns correct user+provider; unknown ID → ErrNotFound\n- Test `DeleteUser`: existing user → deleted, subsequent find returns ErrNotFound; unknown ID → ErrNotFound\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Backend: JWT Email Claim\n\n### Step 5. Extend JWTClaims and CreateJWT\nFile: `backend/web/routes/jwt.go`\n- Add `Email string \\`json:\"email\"\\`` field to `JWTClaims`\n- Change `CreateJWT(user *bizmodels.User)` → `CreateJWT(user *bizmodels.User, email string) (string, error)`; populate `Email` claim.\n\n### Step 6. Update CreateJWT callers\nFile: `backend/web/routes/auth.go`\n- OAuth callback path (existing user): email is `input.Email` (from `webmappers.GothUserToAuthInput`). Pass it to `CreateJWT`.\n- Registration path: email is `authInput.Email` (from `ParsePreRegToken`). Pass it to `CreateJWT`.\n\n### Step 7. Update JWT-related tests\nFile: `backend/web/routes/jwt_test.go` (if exists) and `auth_test.go`\n- Update any `CreateJWT` calls to pass email.\n- Add assertion that decoded JWT payload includes `email`.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Backend: Handler & Route\n\n### Step 8. Add DeleteAccount to AuthHandler\nFile: `backend/business-logic/handlers/auth_handler.go`\n- `func (h *AuthHandler) DeleteAccount(ctx context.Context, userID int64) error`\n  1. Call `h.users.FindByUserID(ctx, userID)` to get user + primary provider.\n  2. If provider.ProviderEmail == h.adminEmail → return `businesslogic.ErrUnauthorized`\n  3. Call `h.users.DeleteUser(ctx, userID)`\n  4. Log `slog.Info(\"auth: user account deleted\", \"user_id\", userID)` — no PII in log\n  5. Return nil on success; wrap any repo errors with `fmt.Errorf(\"AuthHandler.DeleteAccount: %w\", err)`\n\n### Step 9. Register DELETE /user/account route\nFile: `backend/web/routes/auth.go`\n- Add `huma.Register(protectedAPI, huma.Operation{OperationID: \"delete-account\", Method: http.MethodDelete, Path: \"/user/account\", DefaultStatus: http.StatusNoContent, ...}, ...)` on `protectedAPI`\n- No viewmodel needed (empty input/output); extract `claims.UserID` from context; call `h.DeleteAccount`; map error with `MapError`.\n- The `AuthHandler` parameter is already available (passed to `RegisterAuthRoutes`).\n\n### Step 10. Handler tests\nFile: `backend/business-logic/handlers/auth_handler_test.go`\n- `TestDeleteAccount_Success`: mock `FindByUserID` returning non-admin user, mock `DeleteUser` returning nil → expect nil error\n- `TestDeleteAccount_AdminBlocked`: mock `FindByUserID` returning admin user → expect `ErrUnauthorized`, `DeleteUser` NOT called\n- `TestDeleteAccount_UserNotFound`: mock `FindByUserID` returning `ErrNotFound` → expect wrapped ErrNotFound\n- `TestDeleteAccount_DeleteFails`: mock `FindByUserID` OK, mock `DeleteUser` returning error → expect wrapped error\n\n### Step 11. Route tests\nFile: `backend/web/routes/auth_test.go`\n- `TestDeleteAccount_NoAuth`: DELETE /user/account without JWT → 401\n- `TestDeleteAccount_Success`: valid JWT, mock returns success → 204 No Content\n- `TestDeleteAccount_AdminForbidden`: valid JWT for admin user, mock returns ErrUnauthorized → 403\n- `TestDeleteAccount_NotFound`: valid JWT, mock returns ErrNotFound → 404\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — Frontend\n\n### Step 12. Regenerate API client\nRun: `npm run generate:api` from `frontend/` (after backend OpenAPI spec is updated by the new endpoint)\n- This adds `deleteUserAccount()` to `DefaultService` in `src/lib/api/`\n\n### Step 13. Update auth store\nFile: `frontend/src/stores/auth.ts`\n- Add `email` to the `User` interface and `user` ref\n- In `handleCallback`: decode and store `payload.email ?? ''` into `user.email`\n- Add `deleteAccount()` async action:\n  - Set a `deleting` ref to true, clear `deleteError`\n  - Call `DefaultService.deleteUserAccount()` (generated client)\n  - On success: clear all auth state (same as `logout()` body, minus backend call)\n  - On error: set `deleteError` with user-friendly message\n  - Always set `deleting` to false in finally block\n- Export `deleting` and `deleteError` reactive refs\n\n### Step 14. Update ProfileSettingsView\nFile: `frontend/src/views/ProfileSettingsView.vue`\n- Import Dialog, DialogContent, DialogHeader, DialogTitle, DialogDescription, DialogFooter, DialogClose, Button, Input from shadcn/vue components\n- State: `dialogOpen` ref, `confirmEmail` ref, `isConfirmed` computed (confirmEmail.value.toLowerCase() === auth.user?.email?.toLowerCase())\n- \"Delete my account\" button (variant=\"destructive\") opens the dialog\n- Dialog content:\n  - Title: \"Delete your account\"\n  - Description: explains irreversible deletion, shows `auth.user?.email` prominently\n  - Input field: v-model=confirmEmail, placeholder=\"Type your email to confirm\"\n  - Footer: Cancel (DialogClose) + \"Confirm deletion\" (variant=\"destructive\", :disabled=\"!isConfirmed || auth.deleting\")\n  - Error display div (v-if=\"auth.deleteError\")\n  - On \"Confirm deletion\" click: call `auth.deleteAccount()`, on success redirect to '/' via router with a query param or use a toast\n- After deletion, clear dialog and redirect to home\n\n### Step 15. Frontend tests\nFile: `frontend/src/stores/auth.spec.ts` (or alongside auth.ts)\n- Test `deleteAccount` success: mocks `DefaultService.deleteUserAccount`, verifies store cleared\n- Test `deleteAccount` error: verifies `deleteError` is set, state not cleared\n\nFile: `frontend/src/views/ProfileSettingsView.spec.ts`\n- Test dialog opens on button click\n- Test confirm button disabled when email doesn't match\n- Test confirm button enabled when email matches (case-insensitive)\n- Test loading state shown during deletion\n- Test error message shown on failure\n\n---\n\n## Relevant Files\n\n- `backend/business-logic/interfaces/user_repository.go` — add FindByUserID, DeleteUser\n- `backend/business-logic/interfaces/mocks/mock_user_repository.go` — add mock methods\n- `backend/infrastructure/pg/repositories/user_repository.go` — implement both methods\n- `backend/infrastructure/pg/repositories/user_repository_test.go` — add repo tests\n- `backend/business-logic/handlers/auth_handler.go` — add DeleteAccount method\n- `backend/business-logic/handlers/auth_handler_test.go` — add handler tests\n- `backend/web/routes/jwt.go` — add Email to JWTClaims, update CreateJWT signature\n- `backend/web/routes/auth.go` — update CreateJWT callers, register DELETE /user/account\n- `backend/web/routes/auth_test.go` — update existing tests + add route tests\n- `frontend/src/lib/api/` — regenerated (do not edit manually)\n- `frontend/src/stores/auth.ts` — add email, deleteAccount, deleting, deleteError\n- `frontend/src/views/ProfileSettingsView.vue` — implement full deletion flow\n\n## Verification\n1. `go test ./...` passes with ≥95% coverage on business-logic/ and infrastructure/ packages\n2. `go vet ./...` passes\n3. Manually: authenticated user can open dialog, must type exact email (case-insensitive) to enable button, on confirm → 204, all state cleared, redirected to home\n4. Manually: admin user's \"Delete my account\" returns 403 (dialog shows error)\n5. `npm run test` passes with ≥80% coverage on auth store and ProfileSettingsView\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VAW9WncLV1cszTsdL3XpfR__vscode-1773735574206","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

